<div class="entryuserpic"><img src="http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/64713697/6147639" title="" alt=""height="100" width="100"  /></div></div>

<div class="entrycontent">Considering this post originated in Boston, I will defer from commenting on CA.  In MA a motorcycle cannot pass another car in the same lane.  <br /><br />Chapter 89: Section 4A - Driving vehicles in a single lane; motorcycles, riding and passing Section 4A. The operators of motorcycles shall not ride abreast of more than one other motorcycle, shall ride single file when passing, and shall not pass any other motor vehicle within the same lane, except another motorcycle.</div>

